-- Utility Edison Hires Banks to Sell Seven-Year Bonds Denominated in Euros
-- B y   C a r o l i n e   H y d e
-- 2010-11-03T08:38:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-03/utility-edison-hires-banks-to-sell-seven-year-bonds-denominated-in-euros.html
Edison SpA plans to sell seven-year
bonds in euros, according to a banker involved in the
transaction.  Banca IMI SpA, BNP Paribas SA, Credit Agricole CIB,
Mediobanca SpA, Societe Generale SA and UniCredit SpA are
managing the sale.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Caroline Hyde at 
 chyde3@bloomberg.net  